      "side": 1,
      "message": "This looks like when we ship the system image, and run the emulator from the AVD manager, or from command line with -avd \u003cavdname\u003e, it will look in ~/.android/ for the parameters. Is this intended?\n\nI thought it would be found either in $ANDROID_SDK_ROOT/system-images/android-28/google_apis/x86_64/VerifiedBootParams.textproto or ~/.android/avd/api28.avd/VerifiedBootParams.textproto.\n\nI\u0027m asking b/c if we have multiple different system images with different verified boot parameters on the system, it kind of looks like it would be overwritten or stale, since theres\u0027 only one ~/.android.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 239,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 239,
        "endChar": 53
      },
      "revId": "b986bb4f018e1c080bffca752621439d4ed2351c",
